	* Eris/TerrainMod.cpp: Don't include Eris library headers using ""
	  as this won't work on the Mac build.

2009-01-22  Al Riddoch  <alriddoch@googlemail.com>

	* Eris/BaseConnection.cpp: Null pointers after they have been deleted,
	  and don't assert that codec and encoder are there on a
	  disconnecting connection. Clean out hard tabs.
	  Add comments explaining why member deletes are conditional.
	  Always use {} round if clauses especially if there are multiple
	  lines. Assert a pointer is valid before deleting it.

	* Eris/Connection.cpp: Add a comment about an assertion.
	  Clean up a style inconsistency. Always use {} round if clauses.

	* Eris/Connection.h: Make a private section protected to allow
	  more testing.

	* test/Connection_unittest.cpp: Add test coverage for Connection
	  methods connect(), disconnect(), gotData() and send().

